  "texts": [
    "However, the sentence-level score aggregation-based BERT suffers from the loss of important information as well as relevant judgment.• Passage-level score aggregation: The state-of-the-art approaches [108,136,147] of this kind rely on segmenting long documents into small overlapping passages.",
    "These passages are formed by considering the passage length and the stride length to prevent passages of a long document from becoming independent of one another.",
    "Hence, document-level retrieval can be realized by aggregating passage scores [108,136,147].",
    "Dai • Passage-level representation aggregation: State-of-the-art approaches [23,112] that fall into this category rely on aggregating the passage representations rather than the passage scores.Li et al.",
    "proposed passage representation aggregation for document reranking (PARADE) [23]."
  ],
